---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Neighbors from "../../components/Neighbors.astro";
---

<Layout title="Cryptography" favicon="🔐">
  <main>

    <a href="/reading/" class="text-sm mb-4 inline-block">&larr; back to reading</a>

    <h1>🔐 Cryptography</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 mb-2">Based on <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cryptography">Wikipedia</a>, licensed <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/">CC BY-SA 4.0</a>.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-400 mb-6">From XOR ciphers to TEE enclaves. Each chapter builds one layer of the modern security stack, with runnable code and diagrams.</p>

    <!-- SVG: plaintext -> lock -> ciphertext -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 400 120" class="w-full max-w-md" style="font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;">
        <!-- Plaintext label -->
        <text x="40" y="65" text-anchor="middle" fill="#86efac" font-size="12">plaintext</text>
        <!-- Arrow to lock -->
        <line x1="80" y1="60" x2="150" y2="60" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-opacity="0.5"/>
        <polygon points="150,56 158,60 150,64" fill="currentColor" fill-opacity="0.5"/>
        <!-- Padlock body -->
        <rect x="165" y="45" width="50" height="35" rx="4" fill="none" stroke="#facc15" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <!-- Padlock shackle -->
        <path d="M 178 45 V 32 A 12 12 0 0 1 202 32 V 45" fill="none" stroke="#facc15" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <!-- Key hole -->
        <circle cx="190" cy="58" r="4" fill="#facc15" fill-opacity="0.4"/>
        <line x1="190" y1="62" x2="190" y2="72" stroke="#facc15" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-opacity="0.4"/>
        <!-- Key below lock -->
        <line x1="210" y1="95" x2="240" y2="95" stroke="#f59e0b" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <circle cx="245" cy="95" r="5" fill="none" stroke="#f59e0b" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <line x1="215" y1="95" x2="215" y2="90" stroke="#f59e0b" stroke-width="1"/>
        <line x1="222" y1="95" x2="222" y2="90" stroke="#f59e0b" stroke-width="1"/>
        <text x="228" y="110" text-anchor="middle" fill="#f59e0b" font-size="10" fill-opacity="0.6">key</text>
        <!-- Arrow from lock to ciphertext -->
        <line x1="222" y1="60" x2="290" y2="60" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-opacity="0.5"/>
        <polygon points="290,56 298,60 290,64" fill="currentColor" fill-opacity="0.5"/>
        <!-- Ciphertext label -->
        <text x="340" y="65" text-anchor="middle" fill="#f87171" font-size="12">ciphertext</text>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-700">
            <th class="text-left py-2 pr-3 text-gray-400">Chapter</th>
            <th class="text-left py-2 pr-3 text-gray-400">One sentence</th>
            <th class="text-left py-2 text-gray-400"></th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="bg-zinc-900"><td colspan="3" class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300 font-semibold">Part 1: Symmetric primitives</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/cryptography/crypto-01/">1. Symmetric Ciphers</a></td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">XOR, Caesar, substitution: encryption and decryption share the same secret</td>
            <td><a href="/reading/cryptography/crypto-01/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🔐</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/cryptography/crypto-02/">2. Block Ciphers</a></td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Feistel networks and AES: fixed-size blocks, multiple rounds, diffusion and confusion</td>
            <td><a href="/reading/cryptography/crypto-02/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🔐</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/cryptography/crypto-03/">3. Hash Functions</a></td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">One-way compression: any input to a fixed-length fingerprint, no way back</td>
            <td><a href="/reading/cryptography/crypto-03/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🔐</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/cryptography/crypto-04/">4. MACs and Authentication</a></td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">HMAC: a keyed hash that proves the message was not tampered with</td>
            <td><a href="/reading/cryptography/crypto-04/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🔐</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-zinc-900"><td colspan="3" class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300 font-semibold">Part 2: Public-key cryptography</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/cryptography/crypto-05/">5. Key Exchange</a></td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Diffie-Hellman: two strangers agree on a shared secret over a public channel</td>
            <td><a href="/reading/cryptography/crypto-05/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🔐</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/cryptography/crypto-06/">6. RSA</a></td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Public key encrypts, private key decrypts: the factoring problem makes it hard</td>
            <td><a href="/reading/cryptography/crypto-06/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🔐</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-zinc-900"><td colspan="3" class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300 font-semibold">Part 3: Protocols and trust</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-500">7. Digital Signatures</td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-600">Sign with a private key, verify with the public key: non-repudiation</td>
            <td></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-500">8. Certificates and PKI</td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-600">Certificate chains, root CAs, and the web of trust</td>
            <td></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-500">9. TLS</td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-600">The handshake: key exchange + authentication + symmetric encryption</td>
            <td></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-500">10. Zero-Knowledge Proofs</td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-600">Prove you know a secret without revealing it</td>
            <td></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-500">11. Secure Multi-Party Computation</td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-600">Jointly compute a function without sharing inputs</td>
            <td></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-500">12. TEE Enclaves</td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-600">Hardware-enforced isolation: code runs in a tamper-proof enclave</td>
            <td></td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>


    <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mt-8">📺 Video lectures: <a href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC1usFRN4LCMcfIV7UjHNuQg">Christof Paar: Introduction to Cryptography</a></p>

    <Neighbors>
    <ul class="neighbors">
      <li><a href="/reading/number-theory/">&#35; Number Theory</a> &mdash; RSA is Euler's theorem, key exchange is discrete logarithm</li>
      <li><a href="/reading/abstract-algebra/">🔗 Abstract Algebra</a> &mdash; elliptic curves are abelian groups</li>
      <li><a href="/reading/information-theory/">📡 Information Theory</a> &mdash; Shannon's perfect secrecy is information-theoretic security</li>
      <li><a href="/reading/theory-of-computation/">🔀 Theory of Computation</a> &mdash; computational hardness assumptions underlie every scheme</li>
    </ul>
    </Neighbors>

  </main>
</Layout>
